    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Pseudoacanthocereus brasiliensis are wounds, which are often caused by bacterial infections such as Staphylococcus aureus and Escherichia coli, and can be treated with the plant's antimicrobial properties, reducing inflammation and promoting tissue repair through the activation of various signaling pathways. Pseudoacanthocereus brasiliensis is also used to treat fever, as it contains flavonoids and phenolic acids that exhibit antipyretic activity by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. Additionally, the plant's antiseptic properties make it effective in treating burns, which are characterized by severe tissue damage and can be alleviated by the plant's ability to promote wound healing and reduce the risk of infection. Furthermore, Pseudoacanthocereus brasiliensis has been shown to exhibit analgesic and anti-inflammatory properties, making it a potential treatment for pain caused by inflammation, such as arthritis. The plant's antioxidant properties also make it effective in treating oxidative stress-related conditions, including cancer.",
