    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Pseudoacanthocereus brasiliensis are anti-inflammatory and antioxidant, which contribute to its antimicrobial activity, antiproliferative effects against cancer cells, and its potential in treating wounds and skin conditions. The bioactive compounds responsible for these properties include flavonoids and phenolic acids, which have been shown to exhibit strong antioxidant activity. The antiproliferative effects of Pseudoacanthocereus brasiliensis are attributed to the presence of saponins, which have been found to inhibit the growth of cancer cells. The antimicrobial activity of this plant is due to the presence of volatile oils, which have been shown to exhibit antibacterial and antifungal properties. The antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties of Pseudoacanthocereus brasiliensis also make it a potential treatment for conditions such as dermatitis and eczema, where the bioactive compound responsible is likely to be a flavonoid.",
